10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Bloodbath &amp; Beyond</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/30747147.267413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDcvYmVkLWJhdGgtYmV5b25kLXNvbGQtc29tZS1zdG9jaz9jbXBp=
ZD1CQkQwMzA2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2x=
ldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB806151db" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked</a> last <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30747147.267413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDgvYmVkLWJhdGgtYmV5b25kLWdvdC1pdHMt=
ZGVhbC1kb25lP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMDYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXR=
tX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdH=
VmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB166631bf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  month</a> about a death-s=
piral-ish financing at Bed Bath &amp; Beyond Inc. The company was days away=
 from bankruptcy when a deal arrived: Hudson Bay Capital Management<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0would put about $1 billion into Bed Bath in exchange for vast amo=
unts of stock. But not, like, Hudson Bay wrote a check for $1 billion and B=
ed Bath gave it a pile of stock. Rather, the deal is that Bed Bath got $225=
 million, and in exchange it would basically give Hudson Bay stock each day=
, and Hudson Bay would sell it, until Hudson Bay got back its $225 million =
plus a nice little return. The mechanics were more complicated than that =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0they involve convertible preferred stock with a floating con=
version rate, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0but that=E2=80=99s the economic intuition=
. Each day Hudson Bay can convert some of its $225 million investment into =
shares at below the market price that day, and then sell those shares=C2=A0=
to pay itself back with interest.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footn=
ote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !i=
mportant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;"=
>
<span>[2]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If all goes well, Hudson Bay will put up more =
money: as much as $800 million more, in stages, over the course of the year=
. Each time, it will put up some money and get the same deal again, convert=
ible preferred stock that it can convert over time into common shares at a =
discount to the market price each day. It keeps doing that until Bed Bath h=
as gotten the full billion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are limits to this. This plan involves i=
ssuing hundreds of=C2=A0millions of shares of Bed Bath stock; when the plan=
 was announced, there were only 117.3 million shares outstanding. So Bed Ba=
th would be issuing many times more shares to Hudson Bay than it currently =
has outstanding, and Hudson Bay would be dumping them, relentlessly, over t=
he course of the year. Relentlessly dumping stock will move the price down.=
=C2=A0The stock closed at $5.86 per share on Feb. 6, as this plan was being=
 finalized. It closed at $1.49 this past Friday.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This doesn=E2=80=99t matter=C2=A0<em>too=C2=A0=
</em>much for Bed Bath, since the alternative seems to have been a messy ba=
nkruptcy without much prospect=C2=A0for recovery for the equity: <em>Diluti=
ng=C2=A0</em>the shareholders, and driving down the stock price, is a relat=
ively good outcome. And it doesn=E2=80=99t matter too much for Hudson Bay, =
because it gets to buy the stock at a discount to whatever the stock price =
is: If the stock is at $1.49, it gets to convert at $1.37, so it makes 12 c=
ents per share.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgrou=
nd-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it does matter a little, because (1) Bed B=
ath cannot issue infinite shares (it seems to be capped at about 780 millio=
n) and (2) Hudson Bay cannot sell them at infinitesimal prices.<a class=3D"=
footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !impo=
rtant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0In a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/307=
47147.267413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMj=
ItMDUtMTEvdGVycmEtZmxvcHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1b=
T1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWln=
bj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB77130cdb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  true death sp=
iral</a>, Hudson Bay would keep getting more shares and dumping them, the s=
tock would go to zero, and everyone would be sad, but that is not the deal =
here.=C2=A0In fact, the conversion price is floored at $0.716 per share: If=
 the stock trades at, say, $0.60, Hudson Bay will lose money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This gives Hudson Bay some incentive to manage=
 its sales of the stock: It can=E2=80=99t dump too much too fast, or it wil=
l drive the price too far down and lose money.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand Hudson Bay was not going to =
put up $1 billion all at once and risk losing it all if the stock price cra=
tered. Bed Bath only got the first $225 million upfront; the rest comes in =
over time, and only if the stock can still support the trade. Specifically,=
 Hudson Bay doesn=E2=80=99t have to put up any more money unless the stock =
has consistently=C2=A0traded=C2=A0above $1.25, for the first few tranches, =
or $1.50, for the remainder.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !import=
ant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so=C2=A0the price is hovering right around=
 there.=C2=A0If it goes up any more, Hudson Bay is incentivized to convert =
and bang out as much stock as it can. If it goes down much more, the mutual=
ly beneficial deal =E2=80=94=C2=A0Hudson Bay gets to buy tons of stock at a=
 discount, Bed Bath gets cash =E2=80=94=C2=A0stops working. So here we are.=
 Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/30747147.267413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
MjMtMDMtMDMvYmVkLWJhdGgtYmV5b25kLXMtdGFua2luZy1zdG9jay1wdXRzLWhlZGdlLWZ1bmQ=
tcmVzY3VlLWF0LXJpc2s_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbW=
FpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb=
25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf031489a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Eliza Ronalds-Hann=
on reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The financial lifeline that pulled Bed Bath &a=
mp; Beyond Inc. from the brink of bankruptcy last month is already at risk =
because of the retailer=E2=80=99s tumbling stock price. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The additional cash has strings attached. Amon=
g them: Future injections are contingent on Bed Bath &amp; Beyond maintaini=
ng a weighted average stock price of at least $1.25 or $1.50, depending on =
the timing, according to a regulatory filing. The deal terms allow Hudson B=
ay to waive those conditions if it wants.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But keeping the stock price above those thresh=
olds may not be easy. It has already tumbled over 70% since Feb. 6 and clos=
ed as low as $1.41 on Tuesday. The shares ended Thursday at $1.56.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Volume remains very high, though, so someone i=
s still buying, and presumably they=E2=80=99re buying stock that Hudson Bay=
 is selling.</p>
<table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadding=3D=
"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
