s to be the main=C2=A0theory of attracting investors to these funds, so pre=
sumably having to short their ETF in their ETF would attract more investors=
. For me, also, it is funny, and I want it to happen. Are ETFs allowed to s=
hort themselves? Probably? I have no idea but I really hope we=E2=80=99re g=
oing to find out.</p>
